Super Bowl Data Analysis
This project analyzes Super Bowl data using Python and pandas to explore TV viewership trends, game outcomes, and halftime performances.
Key Features:
Merges TV viewership data with Super Bowl dates to track trends over the years.
Visualizes average US viewers for each Super Bowl edition.
Counts and visualizes games with a large point difference (over 40 points).
Analyzes halftime show performances to find which musician performed the most songs.
Tools Used:
Python, pandas, matplotlib
Insights:
Identifies if TV viewership has increased over time.
Highlights trends in Super Bowl scores.
Reveals top-performing halftime musicians.
